<body>
<h1>
Basic Rice
</h1>
<h2>
By: Samara Coleman
</h2>
<p>
Rice is a staple to any dish and goes with just about anything. It can be an enriching source of complex carbohydrates which are important in any balanced diet. There are many variations to its preparation, and somehow, we still manage to mess it up every now and again. Below is a simple and easy to follow recipe that you'll never go wrong with.
</p>
<h2>
Ingredients:
</h2>
<ul>
<li> 1 Cup of Rice (Brown or White)</li>
<li> 2 Cups of Water</li>
<li> 2 tablespoons of Butter</li>
<li> Dash of Salt</li>
</ul>
<h2>
What To Do:
</h2>
<ol>
<li> Put dry rice into bowl and rinse under water until water runs clear</li>
<li> Pour two cups of water into pot and add salt</li>
<li> Cover pot and bring water to a boil with high heat</li>
<li> When water boils, stir in rice slowly</li>
<li> Reduce heat and let rice simmer for 5 to 7 mins or until water is absorbed, stirring occasionally</li>
<li> Remove rice from heat and stir in butter, allowing to melt</li>
<li> Serve</li>
</ol>
